						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab set up in the temple of Basavaṇṇa outside the village.</hi></p>						

						<p>Trailōkyamalla (Sōmēśvara I)—Date lost.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record engraved below No. 35 refers to a subordinate of <hi rend="bold">Trailōkyamalla,</hi> whose name is lost, who was governing the <hi rend="italic">Perjjuṅka</hi> of a division probably <hi rend="bold">Banavāsi 12,000.</hi> It seems to record a gift for oil-lamp and incense to a God. The details are lost. </p>						

						</summary>
